title: Stories of Beowulf Told to the Children
creator: Henrietta Elizabeth Marshall
description: LibriVox recording of Stories of Beowulf Told to the Children, by Henrietta Elizabeth Marshall. Read by LibriVox volunteers. The brave warrior, Beowulf, comes to the aid of King Hrothgar when he hears that Grendel, a horrible monster, is terrorizing the inhabitants of Hart Hall. Beowulf heroically battles Grendel, the Water Witch, and a fierce dragon. (Summary by Laura Caldwell) M4B format available For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
